{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17590608","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17590608"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T09:49:59+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T09:49:59+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15209"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15209","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15209"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.43,0.35,0.11,0.05,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7900"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64612"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7900","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7900"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15209"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50046"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"351"},{"type":"tags","id":"1151"},{"type":"tags","id":"3376"},{"type":"tags","id":"3455"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"8572"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19252"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19255"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21318"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64612","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/64612"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 68-year-old man attends the Gastroenterology clinic for surveillance endoscopy. He has a history of Barrett\u0027s oesophagus and gastro-oesophageal reflux disease. His medications include pantoprazole. On examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. His body mass index is 28 kg/m2.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn endoscopy, a raised, nodular lesion is identified in the distal oesophagus. Biopsies are taken, which show adenocarcinoma.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following histological findings would make the lesion most suitable for endoscopic therapy?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Intramucosal invasion","Submucosal invasion","Muscularis propria invasion","Serosal involvement","Lymphovascular invasion"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EEarly oesophageal adenocarcinoma can be treated endoscopically if confined to the mucosa (T1a) without evidence of lymphovascular invasion. The depth of invasion is crucial in determining the appropriate management strategy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntramucosal invasion\u003C/strong\u003E (T1a) has a low risk of lymph node metastasis (less than 2%) and can be safely treated with endoscopic mucosal resection or endoscopic submucosal dissection, provided there is no lymphovascular invasion.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESubmucosal invasion\u003C/strong\u003E (T1b) has a significantly higher risk of lymph node metastasis (approximately 20-30%) and typically requires surgical resection rather than endoscopic therapy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELymphovascular invasion\u003C/strong\u003E indicates a higher risk of metastatic disease and is a contraindication to endoscopic therapy, even if the invasion is superficial.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMuscularis propria invasion\u003C/strong\u003E (T2) and \u003Cstrong\u003Eserosal involvement\u003C/strong\u003E (T3) represent more advanced disease that requires surgical resection and possibly neoadjuvant therapy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe key principle is that endoscopic therapy is only appropriate for early-stage disease confined to the mucosa without high-risk features. This allows for organ preservation while maintaining oncological safety.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Early adenocarcinoma confined to the mucosa (T1a) is amenable to endoscopic therapy.","Depth of invasion is the key determinant for endoscopic versus surgical management of early oesophageal cancer.","Endoscopic mucosal resection is appropriate for lesions confined to the mucosa without lymphovascular invasion."],"references":["di Pietro M, Trudgill N, Vasileiou M, et al. National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) guidance on monitoring and management of Barrett\u2019s oesophagus and stage I oesophageal\u00a0adenocarcinoma. Gut 2024;73:897\u2013909","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50046"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15209"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50046","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/50046"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-24T11:35:05+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-24T11:35:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7900"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64612"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"31","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/31"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf97","na